[1] Fiji ex Philippines
Date: Wed 19 Feb 2020
Source: FBC News [abridged, edited]
https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/news/health/woman-diagnosed-with-measles-after-arrival/


A woman has been placed in home isolation in Suva after having developed measles after arriving into the country from the Philippines on the 9th of this month [February 2020]. This is the 1st case of the disease since 6 Jan [2020], and the Ministry of Health says the patient's husband and son have also been placed on home isolation.

The 35-year-old was well during a health screening at Nadi Airport but developed symptoms of measles the day after her arrival [10 Feb 2020].

The Ministry says that with the Philippines having an ongoing outbreak of measles, it is clear that she became infected with measles in the Philippines and not in Fiji.

[See URL above for locations/times of possible exposure.]

The latest case brings to 28 the total number of cases for the outbreak that began on November 7th last year [2019].

[Byline: Indra Singh]

